 East London - Police in East London have appealed to the public for assistance after a 10-year-old boy, Amila Kawa, of Cambridge location, East London, was reported missing to police on Wednesday. According to information, it is said that he went swimming with his friends on Tuesday afternoon, 04 February, to a nearby dam and he never came back home. "He was last seen wearing blue shorts, black t-shirt and blue flip-flops," said police spokesperson, Captain Mluleki Mbi. "A search team comprising members of the community from Cambridge location, SAPS including police divers were activated to search around the area and the nearby dams. "We appeal to anyone who might assist in locating him to contact Cambridge police station on 043 709 7500 or 08600 10111." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 